text: Nancy Uranga (17 August 1954 - 6 October 1976) was a Cuban fencer. She competed in the women's individual and team foil events at the 1976 Summer Olympics. She was one of the passengers on board Cubana Flight 455, which was brought down by a terrorist attack. ==References== Category:1954 births Category:1976 deaths Category:Cuban female fencers Category:Olympic fencers of Cuba Category:Fencers at the 1976 Summer Olympics Category:People murdered in Barbados Category:Cuban people murdered abroad Category:Cuban terrorism victims Category:Murdered sportspeople Category:Victims of aviation accidents or incidents in Barbados Category:Pan American Games medalists in fencing Category:Pan American Games gold medalists for Cuba Category:Fencers at the 1975 Pan American Games
